Digital Logic
---------------

* Computer Language : 
-----------------------
- A computer compares 1s and 0s but millions or billions of times per second.

- Binary System : The communication that a computer users, a.k.a base-2 numeral system.
- In computer standards - binary is grouped into 8 numbers or bits;
- Bit : Binary digit;
- Bytes : 8 bits; (2 power 8, 256 possibilities); Each byte can store one character;
- ASCII "Charcter to Binary" Chart;


* Character Encoding :
----------------------
- A byte can only store zeros and ones; (256 possibilities);
- Character encoding : Assigns our binary values to characters, so that we as humans can read them; (a.ka. Dictionary)

1. ASCII - oldest character encoding standard; (only needed to use 127 values of a possible 256 values);
a = 01100001
(characters, numbers, punctuations, few special characters);

2. UTF-8 -> (Beyond 256 characters) Prevalent encoding standard used today; Along with ASCII standards it also uses a 
variable number of bytes; 
TF - 8 - built off the unicode standard - character encoding in a consistent manner;

- Emoji : Not possible to mke emojis with a single byte, since only one character can be stores in a byte. UTF-8 allows
us to store a character in more than one byte.

3. Colors - RGB model, In computer language 3 characters are used for the RGB model; Each character represents a shade of 
the color - that color changesthe pixel color on the screen; (8 combinations - provide colors);


* Binary
-------------
 - punch cards - when the loom would reach a hole it would hook the thread underneath - state 1 (on) else state 0 (off);
 - the computers read the punch cards - if there was hole - 1 else 0;
 
 - Today binary system is based on the electricity via transistors allowing electrical signals to pass through. If there's an
 electric voltage - 1 else 0;
 
 - logic gates - aloow our transistors to do more complex tasks, like decide where to send electrical signals depending on
 logical cionditions.
 
 * How to count Binary
 -----------------------
 - Binary is the fundamental communication block of computers. Used in representation, networking, etc;
 
 128  64  32  16  8 4 2 1 ( L -> R - number is double of its right counterpart );
 
 128 + 64 + 32 + 16 + 8 + 4 + 2 + 1 = 255 (255 - to 0 | total 256 values);
 
 Guess the number
 128  64  32  16  8  4  2  1
 0    0   0   0   1  0  1  0   -> 10; ( 2 , 8 are on -> 8 + 2 = 10)
 
 
 let h = 104 -> binary representation
 128  64  32  16  8  4  2  1
 0    1   1   0   1  0  0  0  -> 104 (64 + 32 + 8 = 104)
 
